goal arias said at the time that nothing concrete had been 
achieved 
representatives of the leftwing sandinista government and the 
nicaraguan rebels known as contras agreed on a ceasefire march 23 
under a regional peace plan that ortega and four other central 
american presidents signed in august 1987 
the ceasefire often has been violated but extended by both 
sides most recently by nicaragua unilaterally until aug 30 but 
the two sides have deadlocked on a permanent truce and have failed 
to agree on a site or date for talks since the last round ended 
june 9 
