<TEXT>
the percentage of people using seat belts has 
almost quadrupled in the past five years but fewer than half the 
nations motorists buckle up according to the transportation 
department 
surveys in 19 cities showed that more than 43 percent of us 
motorists use the safety devices the department said attributing 
the major portion of the increase from 11 percent five years ago to 
mandatory seat belt use laws in many states 
a total of 32 states and the district of columbia require 
frontseat occupants of vehicles to wear seat belts 
increasingly public acceptance of safety belts is saving lives 
and preventing injuries transportation secretary jim burnley 
said friday estimating that 4000 lives were saved because of seat 
belt use in 1987 
the 19city survey covered 49095 observations of motorists from 
february through may of this year it showed 434 percent of the 
frontseat occupants wore safety belts according to the 
departments national highway traffic safety administration 
similar surveys in 1982 showed belt use to be at about 11 
percent the agency said 
the survey indicated a wide range of seat belt use with 
motorists most likely to wear their belts in dallas 714 percent 
houston 656 percent and seattle 603 percent the cities with 
the lowest use rate were providence ri 154 percent 
fargomoorhead nd 217 percent and new york city 246 
percent 
belt use was sharply higher in cities where laws require 
motorists to use the belts the agency said it said that in 13 
cities in states with safety belt use laws belt use was 483 
percent while in six cities without such laws it was 304 percent 
here is the rate of belt usage in each of the 19 cities 
surveyed according to the highway safety agency 
cities not covered by a beltuse law 
providence ri 154 percent fargomoorhead nd 217 
percent boston 312 percent atlanta 364 percent birmingham 
ala 395 percent phoenix ariz 406 percent 
cities covered by a beltuse law 
new york 246 percent pittsburgh 281 percent chicago 317 
percent new orleans 433 percent baltimore 467 percent los 
angeles 473 percent minneapolisst paul 478 percent miami 
