before the war the president already had a firm grip on power 
in iraq plagued by political instability for years before the 
baath party took control in 1968 
hussein quickly executed opponents within the leadership shortly 
after assuming power in 1979 and crushed proiranian religious 
fundamentalists in 1980 
mindful of numerous coups against past governments and perhaps 
his own past as an underground fighter hussein has used a huge 
security service to keep watch over dissent 
he also has promoted relatives to several key positions in the 
government and military although he has been quick to dump those 
who proved incompetent or disloyal 
the man who leads the iraqis must be of a quick and nimble 
pace hussein said in 1982 so the others will not step on his 
heels then his back then step on his head and pass him over 
hussein himself took part in an unsuccessful 1959 assassination 
attempt against thenpresident abdulkarim qassem 
the son of poor farmers hussein has combined an iron hand with 
a populist appeal he has a reputation for hard work bravery and 
personal honesty 
state television often spends a half hour or more showing the 
president sitting on a floor chatting with peasants or bouncing 
children on his knee the government has encouraged a cult of 
personality around him 
yet hussein told american researcher christine helms in 1982 
that after watching party members scrambling for power in the 
mid1960s i developed an aversion to power i began to 
loathe it 
husseins outlook was forged by his climb through the 
underground politics of the baath party which advocates arab 
unity socialist economics and rejection of foreign domination 
his policies are essentially pragmatic he told ms helms he 
did not think i had to be basically concerned with ideology 
until 1974 when he was already a senior force in the party 
hussein has gradually improved ties with the west and has 
demanded attention to profits and discipline in the countrys 
sluggish state enterprises 
he is also supremely selfconfident in 1964 still in his 20s 
he led a revolt against the old party leadership which was in 
disarray after being driven from power 
while in hiding i issued a communique on behalf of the 
partys provisional regional command which did not exist giving 
myself the authority to lead the party he told helms 
the war interrupted husseins massive effort to use iraqs oil 
wealth to make the country a modern power 
he has lost 10odd years of his rule in which he could have 
literally transformed the country said a senior diplomat in 
baghdad who spoke on condition of anonymity 
they have given a glimpse of the future to their masses and 
with the war over i think they will be in a hurry to start 
building he said 
