<DOCNO> AP880813-0095 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
here at a glance is a look at burma 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the land burma is about the size of texas and shares frontiers 
with india china thailand and laos resources include fertile 
soil timber oil and other minerals rangoon with a population of 
35 million is the capital and largest city mandalay in the 
heart of the country is the secondlargest city and the center of 
traditional culture 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people most of the 38 million people are burmans 
important minorities include chinese indians karens shans chins 
and kachins about 85 percent of the people practice buddhism with 
minorities adhering to islam and christianity 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy per capita income is less than 200 a year making 
burma one of the worlds poorest nations it once was the worlds 
leading rice exporter but it experienced food shortages in 1987 
burmas debt has climbed to more than 3 billion 
the black market fueled by smuggled goods from thailand and 
china overshadows the official economy 
burmas economic failure is generally attributed to poor 
government management and a crippling war against several ethnic 
minorities seeking autonomy japan and west germany are major aid 
donors and the united states has a modest assistance program 
mainly in the antidrug area 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history burmas golden age was the 12th century when its 
kings built the spectacular temples of pagan britain ruled it from 
1886 to 1948 after a postindependence experiment with democracy 
a military coup in 1962 brought gen ne win to power he imposed 
isolationism military control and socialist economics 
ne win remained as leader until his resignation july 23 
following antigovernment demonstrations he was replaced by 
retired army general sein lwin who resigned today after nationwide 
antigovernment riots 
burma seeks to maintain a strictly neutralist policy and keep 
out most foreign influences including joint ventures with foreign 
companies it has been nicknamed asias hermit tourists are 
allowed to stay only one week 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP880813-0096 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
massachusetts republicans have produced a 
video attacking michael dukakis and plan to distribute it to other 
states delegations at the republican national convention to get 
the truth out about the democratic nominee 
the 10minute video which will be unveiled tuesday by 
republican national chairman frank fahrenkopf jr and state gop 
chairman ray shamie shows the truth rather than the myth that 
dukakis likes to perpetuate shamie said 
he talks about things puts a nice spin on them but the facts 
are quite different what were doing is debunking many of his 
statements shamie said in a preconvention telephone interview 
joseph malone the republican senate candidate trying to unseat 
sen edward m kennedy dmass said other states gop chairmen 
will get copies and each chairman will use it to get the truth 
out about mike dukakis 
it will point out what mike dukakis said in his speech about 
protecting the environment then point to the fact that 
massachusetts has the most polluted harbor in the nation in the 
boston harbor and the governor ignored that fact as the harbor 
became more and more polluted malone said 
it will point out his statements on balancing the budget and 
then point to the recent budget crisis in massachusetts he said 
were very familiar with the miracle shamie said a 
deriding reference to the states economic rebound that dukakis 
takes partial credit for on the presidential campaign trail 
</TEXT>
