article mikoyan appeared to be clearing his father of possible 
guilt in stalins purges 
mikoyan could not help but realize that he shared direct 
political responsibility for the establishment of stalins absolute 
power and consequently for spreading over the country a regime of 
lawlessness the younger mikoyan wrote 
however the historian added for many the hour of the great 
redemption has come 
he said it was clear that stalin had support including that of 
his father in carrying out his acts of repression but he said 
the support was obtained through blackmail either join the team or 
be purged often violently 
mikoyan recalled that at a 1937 communist party meeting his 
father was appointed to draft a resolution condemning nikolai 
bukharin a close associate of vladimir i lenin who led the 1917 
revolution that brought the communists to power 
the historian suggests that his father agreed to the fatal 
resolution because it already had been prepared he had no choice 
but to go up to the rostrum or down into the grave bukharin 
was shot to death in 1938 
stalin later banished mikoyan an armenian to the armenian 
capital of yerevan for communion with repression the historian 
wrote 
mikoyan considered suicide his son recalled but decided 
against it to spare his wife and children from suffering because of 
their ties to a disgraced enemy of the people 
instead mikoyan decided to devote his energy to working within 
the system in helping the people by building socialism and 
modernizing soviet industry the historian wrote 
the elder mikoyan was named foreign trade commissioner and 
insisted that the secret police keep away from workers he 
supervised they were spared from waiting for a nighttime ring at 
the door the younger mikoyan wrote 
the elder mikoyan according to the historian also intervened 
to spare the lives of his friends condemned under stalins purges 
after stalins death mikoyan and nikita s khrushchev alone 
pushed for full condemnation of the dictator and rehabilitation of 
his victims the historian said in defense of his father 
in 1956 mikoyan gave a speech condemning stalins cult of 
personality and was also instrumental in staving off an attempt 
to oust khrushchev from the soviet leadership a year later mikoyan 
wrote 
for all this he wrote his father should be praised 
what choices he asked did his father have to perish as an 
enemy of the people and be posthumously rehabilitated or to 
survive to rehabilitate the living and dead finally to do 
something that would help the renewal of the society even in our 
times 
</TEXT>
