rain was scattered along the mississippi valley on saturday and 
along the southern east coast and central appalachians and there 
was more high humidity and record heat across the eastern half of 
the nation 
moisture from the gulf of mexico and atmospheric disturbance 
produced heavy showers and thunderstorms over the middle 
mississippi valley and near a stationary front from wisconsin 
across minnesota to north dakota 
showers and thunderstorms spread along the southern atlantic 
coast from florida to the carolinas and a few showers and 
thunderstorms developed from west virginia to western new york 
about an inch of rain fell in just one hour at both sioux falls 
sd and key west fla st peters mo near st louis got more 
than threequarters of an inch of rain most of it in just 10 
minutes 
alexandria minn got 183 inches of rain in the six hours up 
to 2 pm edt while park falls wis got 122 inches and sioux 
falls sd got 101 inches 
during the night in northern minnesota 350 inches fell at 
hibbing and more than 4 inches fell at grand rapids and nashwak 
a tropical depression had formed off the florida coast but ship 
reports and other observations indicated that it was poorly 
organized and no significant change in strength was expected into 
sunday 
detroit and williamsport pa both hit 90 degrees saturday for 
the 37th day this summer for detroit and and 38th time for 
williamsport many other cities have similar experiences this 
summer 
temperatures rose above 100 degrees over parts of western 
oklahoma and southwestern kansas altus air force base okla 
reached 105 degrees at 2 pm cdt 
