<TEXT>
two young men died in the past five weeks while 
running races in sweltering heat as part of a competition that pits 
company teams against one another authorities said 
fred lebow head of the new york road runners club said the 
men age 23 and 24 were nonrunners who competed without adequate 
preparation for the 3mile races 
organizers acknowledged that participants in the second race 
were not told that someone had died three weeks earlier in the 
first race 
the races in central park which drew thousands of competitors 
were sponsored by the manufacturers hanover trust co as part of 
its corporate challenge series 
anthony mezzina 24 of north bergen nj an employee of the 
manhattan brokerage firm spear leeds amp kellogg collapsed during 
the race july 14 and died a day later 
david reynolds 23 of bergenfield nj a technical writer for 
glasgal communications in northvale nj collapsed shortly after 
completing the aug 4 corporate challenge race he died three days 
later 
the deaths were disclosed friday in an article in new york 
newsday 
temperatures were in the 80s at the time of both races 
lebow said he and other race officials tried to warn the 10000 
runners in the aug 4 race about the dangers of running in the 
heat but didnt disclose the earlier death both of the 
participants who died had signed waivers stating they were in good 
shape and had trained for the race lebow said 
dr andres rodriguez the road runners clubs medical director 
said he distributed a medical alert to team captains aug 3 
warning of the risks i didnt think it was my place to call 
attention to the first death he said 
after the first death the day after a july 14 race team 
captains were told to warn runners about running in extreme heat 
but werent told of the death 
according to hanovers john getzoff the races are designed to 
pit teams from various corporations in a friendly spirit of 
competition the races are held in 13 us cities as well as 
dublin ireland oslo norway and london top teams compete in a 
championship race in new york each november 
