the roy high school soccer team played soccer 
so long they forgot who and where they were and at times even 
forgot how to play 
their more than 75hour effort was an attempt to get into the 
guinness book of world records for the longest soccer game ever 
played 
the team began play monday at noon seventyfive hours 30 
minutes and more than 520 goals later the players came off the 
field thursday afternoon with what they hope will hold up as a 
world record 
the official record of 74 hours is held by a team from wales 
of course theres joy and excitement at breaking the record 
but thats subsided as weve reached the moment said coach scott 
snelson who joined in the marathon so there would be 22 players 
enough for two teams now drowsiness aches and pains have taken 
over 
he said that during the ordeal the team battled fatigueinduced 
hallucinations and illness snelson said one team member tried to 
build sand castles with the dirt near one of the goals another 
imagined he was a small boy again playing with his cars and trucks 
four players dropped out but rules for the record attempt 
allowed eight players to leave the game without disqualification 
snelson said 
