<TEXT>
king hussein met with plo leaders saturday 
to discuss future relations after jordans move to sever ties with 
the israelioccupied territories jordans official news agency 
said 
hussein announced two weeks ago he was ending administrative 
links with the israelioccupied west bank and gaza strip where 15 
million palestinians live 
the news agency said hussein met with mahmoud abbas abdullah 
hourani and mohammed milhem all members of the palestine 
liberation organizations executive committee and hani alhassan 
a senior adviser to plo chairman yasser arafat 
the delegation presented to the king a full evaluation on the 
palestinians current situation and the plo directives following 
jordans recent measures to sever legal and administrative ties 
with the west bank the agency said 
it also said the plos recent actions enhanced the 
organizations role worldwide and gave it an international 
prominence 
the agency said the king explained to the delegation the 
national motives and considerations of the jordanian moves and the 
stable position of this country toward the palestinian issue 
no details on the positions of the two sides were given 
hussein said he was stepping aside to give the plo 
responsibility for the west bank which he ruled from 1948 until 
the israeli military occupied it in the 1967 middle east war 
jordan had kept strong ties to the territory despite the israeli 
occupation and us officials and some israelis hoped that a joint 
jordanianpalestinian delegation could be included in future peace 
talks 
in severing ties the king halted payments to government workers 
in the occupied west bank and gaza strip suspended the lower house 
of parliament with its 30 west bank representatives out of 60 and 
eliminated a ministry devoted solely to west bank affairs 
the moves gave rise to speculation that hussein might be trying 
to set up the plo for failure by inviting it to assume 
responsibilities it cannot fulfill jordan which fought a war in 
197071 to expel palestinian commandos from its territory has a 
history of strained relations with the plo 
no concrete decisions or actions were announced after saturdays 
meeting the official news agency said only that the plo delegation 
expressed the plos appreciation for the kings considerations 
and his interest in supporting the palestinian issue and the rights 
of its people 
