reservation market has allowed 12 smaller carriers to proceed with 
a 300000 antitrust suit 
us district judge edward rafeedie on friday also found 
sufficient evidence of predatory pricecutting and price 
discrimination in americans sabre reservation system to proceed to 
trial on those claims 
sabre along with united airlines reservation system delivers 
most airlines tickets sold in the united states 
smaller airlines which pay fees for tickets booked through the 
systems contend that american and united abuse their domination in 
the computer reservation market by charging high fees and imposing 
restrictions that make it difficult for travel agents to switch to 
rival systems 
american and united counter that the fees are needed to 
compensate for the millions of dollars invested in computers and 
data banks american says it has invested 400 million in sabre 
the judges decision means a jury may decide whether american 
has engaged in anticompetitive business practices and it left open 
the possibility that a jury can decide whether united may have 
engaged in a limited monopoly over the computer reservation market 
the judge dismissed claims that american and united wielded a 
